-- Global economy gradually recovering: China's Li
-- 
-- Sun Sep 12, 2010 11:25pm EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2010/09/13/us-china-economy-li-idUSTRE68C0JN20100913

 

 BEIJING  (Reuters) - The global economy is gradually emerging from crisis but needs more-open markets and less trade friction, Chinese Vice-Premier Li Keqiang said on Monday. 

 Li was speaking at an event to mark the 30th anniversary of China's partnership with the World Bank. (Reporting by Langi Chiang and  Simon Rabinovitch ; Editing by  Alan Wheatley )